</span></p><img alt="pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp__PID:81d61092-7a41-4a8d-8f72-32c680089f8e" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/pfas-environmental-contamination-toxic-soil.webp?v=1739901854&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.5" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image4" class="sc-EROOM jwpaTY pf-240_" store="[object Object]"/></div></div><div class="pf-c pf-sm-hide pf-hide" style="--c-xs:3;--c-sm:2;--c-md:4;--c-lg:3"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-241_ pf-sm-hide pf-hide"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-242_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><strong>Glossary<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);">keywords</span></strong><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);"></span><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);"></span></span></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-244_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Bioaccumulation:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The process by which toxic substances, such as PFAS, build up in the tissues of living organisms over time.

</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-246_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Emissions:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The release of pollutants, including PFAS, into the air, water, or soil, often from industrial activities.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-248_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Exposure:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The act of coming into contact with PFAS through food, water, air, or consumer products.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-250_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Greenwashing:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);"> A deceptive marketing practice where brands falsely claim to be environmentally friendly while still engaging in harmful practices.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-252_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Manufacturing:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The industrial process of producing goods, including textiles and packaging, where PFAS are commonly used.

</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-254_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Nonstick:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A coating applied to cookware and packaging to prevent sticking, often achieved using PFAS-based chemicals.

</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-256_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Persistent:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A characteristic meaning that it does not break down easily and remain in the environment and human body for long periods.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-258_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Regulations:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">Laws and policies set by governments to control or limit the use of harmful substances like PFAS.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-260_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Repellency:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The ability of a surface, such as textiles or packaging, to resist water, stains, or grease, often due to PFAS treatments.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-262_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Substitution:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The process of replacing harmful PFAS chemicals with safer alternatives in manufacturing and consumer products.

</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-264_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Textiles:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">Fabrics and materials used in clothing and household products, which are often treated with PFAS for water and stain resistance.



